FBIS3-20258 "drweu060_b_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-060 Document Type:Daily Report 26 Mar 1994 BENELUX Belgium Ministry Issues Travel Advisory for Algeria BR2803133794 Antwerp GAZET VAN ANTWERPEN in Dutch 26 Mar 94 p 6 BR2803133794 Antwerp GAZET VAN ANTWERPEN Language: Dutch Article Type:BFN [Unattributed report: "Foreign Ministry Advises Against Traveling To Algeria"] [Text] The Belgian Foreign Ministry issued an advisory on Friday [25 March] that anyone intending to travel to Algeria should postpone the trip until later, unless it is of the utmost urgency. The Ministry confirmed its concern for "individual security problems in Algeria," and asked Belgians who had not yet been able to leave Algeria to "make every possible effort to guarantee their safety as much as possible and to keep in regular contact with the Belgian Embassy in Algiers."
